00:55:06,936 --> 00:55:09,427
<i>But BB gun mania knows no loyalties.</i>

693
00:55:09,906 --> 00:55:11,874
Uncle! Uncle!

694
00:55:16,846 --> 00:55:17,870
All right, class.

695
00:55:18,315 --> 00:55:20,909
I have your Christmas themes for you.

696
00:55:21,951 --> 00:55:23,316
I'm pleased.

697
00:55:23,920 --> 00:55:26,115
In general, you did very well.

698
00:55:29,292 --> 00:55:32,819
However, I was disappointed
in the margins.

699
00:55:35,465 --> 00:55:37,057
<i>This is it.</i>

700
00:55:38,435 --> 00:55:40,630
<i>"C</i>+<i>"? No, it can't be.</i>

701
00:55:41,071 --> 00:55:42,470
C+?

702
00:55:42,639 --> 00:55:44,664
C+!

703
00:55:52,449 --> 00:55:53,677
<i>Oh, no!</i>

704
00:55:54,851 --> 00:55:56,512
<i>"You'll shoot your eye out"?</i>

705
00:55:58,855 --> 00:56:00,823
<i>My mother</i>
<i>must have gotten to Miss Shields.</i>

706
00:56:00,990 --> 00:56:02,582
<i>There could be no other explanation.</i>

707
00:56:02,859 --> 00:56:06,989
You'll shoot your eye out.
You'll shoot your eye out.

708
00:56:09,566 --> 00:56:13,297
<i>Was there no end to this conspiracy</i>
<i>of irrational prejudice...</i>

709
00:56:13,370 --> 00:56:15,668
<i>against Red Ryder and his peacemaker?</i>

710
00:56:15,872 --> 00:56:20,070
These multiplication questions
were most missed in our last math test.

711
00:56:20,176 --> 00:56:21,734
Would you answer in unison, please?

712
00:56:22,045 --> 00:56:24,946
<i>I was surrounded by happier kids</i>
<i>who were all going to get...</i>

713
00:56:25,048 --> 00:56:26,606
<i>what they wanted for Christmas.</i>

714
00:56:26,983 --> 00:56:28,211
...fifty-six.

715
00:56:58,882 --> 00:57:00,406
Hey, four-eyes!

716
00:57:00,483 --> 00:57:03,043
How'd you like your snowball sandwich?

717
00:57:03,720 --> 00:57:05,711
Maybe you'd like another one!

718
00:57:11,261 --> 00:57:12,250
Listen, jerk.

719
00:57:12,495 --> 00:57:15,794
When I tell you to come, you better come!

720
00:57:17,000 --> 00:57:19,468
What? Are you going to cry now?

721
00:57:19,669 --> 00:57:23,435
Come on, cry baby, cry for me. Come on.

722
00:57:23,807 --> 00:57:25,297
Cry!

723
00:57:25,442 --> 00:57:27,239
<i>Deep in the recesses of my brain...</i>

724
00:57:27,377 --> 00:57:30,744
<i>a tiny red-hot little flame began to grow.</i>

725
00:57:44,494 --> 00:57:45,620
<i>Something had happened.</i>

726
00:57:45,795 --> 00:57:49,788
<i>A fuse blew</i>
<i>and I had gone out of my skull.</i>

727
00:57:58,908 --> 00:58:01,342
I'm telling my dad!

728
00:58:02,745 --> 00:58:04,838
Hey, Ralphie!

729
00:58:11,688 --> 00:58:13,815
Beat him up! Beat him up!

730
00:58:28,304 --> 00:58:30,568
Did you hear what he said?

731
00:58:35,178 --> 00:58:37,612
<i>I have since heard of people under...</i>

732
00:58:37,714 --> 00:58:41,377
<i>extreme duress speaking</i>
<i>in strange tongues.</i>

733
00:58:41,684 --> 00:58:45,142
<i>I became conscious</i>
<i>that a steady torrent of obscenities...</i>

734
00:58:45,321 --> 00:58:49,621
<i>and swearing of all kinds</i>
<i>was pouring out of me as I screamed.</i>

735
00:58:58,468 --> 00:59:00,026
Ralphie!

736
00:59:16,920 --> 00:59:18,785
We're going home. Come on.

737
00:59:37,907 --> 00:59:40,876
Calm down. Come on in here, Ralph.

738
00:59:45,381 --> 00:59:46,814
Put your head down in here.

739
00:59:47,250 --> 00:59:49,411
Come on, get down in here.

740
00:59:50,520 --> 00:59:52,078
Settle down.

741
00:59:54,390 --> 00:59:58,121
I want you to go in there
and lie down in your room for a while.

742
00:59:59,228 --> 01:00:01,355
Ralphie, just settle down.

743
01:00:05,068 --> 01:00:06,831
Here, dry off.

744
01:00:07,070 --> 01:00:09,038
All right, calm down.

745
01:00:09,172 --> 01:00:11,606
All right. Now go lie down.

746
01:00:31,361 --> 01:00:33,921
<i>The light was getting purple</i>
<i>and soft outside.</i>

747
01:00:34,063 --> 01:00:36,896
<i>Almost time for my father</i>
<i>to come home from work.</i>

748
01:00:57,286 --> 01:00:58,878
What's the matter? What you crying for?

749
01:00:59,856 --> 01:01:02,290
Daddy's going to kill Ralphie.

750
01:01:02,892 --> 01:01:04,359
No, he's not.

751
01:01:04,494 --> 01:01:05,859
Yes, he is, too.

752
01:01:05,962 --> 01:01:07,520
No, he's not.

753
01:01:07,630 --> 01:01:11,828
I promise you
Daddy is not going to kill Ralphie.

754
01:01:12,702 --> 01:01:14,226
Why don't you come on out of there?

755
01:01:17,807 --> 01:01:18,967
Would you like some milk?

756
01:01:20,843 --> 01:01:22,572
You would?

757
01:01:29,218 --> 01:01:30,412
Here you go.

758
01:01:31,754 --> 01:01:32,778
All right?

759
01:01:33,489 --> 01:01:36,219
I'll see you later? Okay. Bye.

760
01:01:48,538 --> 01:01:52,201
<i>I heard the car roar up the driveway,</i>
<i>and a wave of terror broke over me.</i>

761
01:01:52,442 --> 01:01:55,468
<i>He'll know what I said,</i>
<i>the awful things that I said.</i>

762
01:01:55,712 --> 01:01:57,509
Get out of here!

763
01:01:58,181 --> 01:02:01,446
Go on home, you mangy mutts.
Get out of here, you rotten, filthy<i>...</i>

764
01:02:01,718 --> 01:02:02,446
Hey, Bumpus!

765
01:02:02,518 --> 01:02:04,986
Get over here and get your stinking dogs!

766
01:02:06,089 --> 01:02:09,149
Hey, come on, what's for dinner?
I'm starving to death.

767
01:02:29,045 --> 01:02:31,673
Well, what happened today?

768
01:02:32,381 --> 01:02:33,712
Where's your glasses?

769
01:02:35,151 --> 01:02:36,812
Did you lose your glasses again?

770
01:02:37,186 --> 01:02:38,118
Ralphie.

771
01:02:38,454 --> 01:02:41,548
Remember, you left these
on the radio again.

772
01:02:41,791 --> 01:02:44,624
Now try not to do that anymore.

773
01:02:45,661 --> 01:02:47,219
So what else happened today?

774
01:02:48,731 --> 01:02:50,130
Nothing much.

775
01:02:50,333 --> 01:02:51,664
Ralphie had a fight.

776
01:02:52,468 --> 01:02:53,230
A fight?

777
01:02:53,436 --> 01:02:54,767
What kind of a fight?

778
01:02:57,206 --> 01:02:59,265
You know how boys are.

779
01:03:00,910 --> 01:03:02,810
I gave him a talking to.

780
01:03:04,213 --> 01:03:07,580
I see that the Bears
are playing Green Bay on Sunday.

781
01:03:09,452 --> 01:03:10,214
Oh, yeah.

782
01:03:10,386 --> 01:03:12,411
Zudock's got tickets. I wish I had.

783
01:03:12,722 --> 01:03:14,622
He'll freeze his keister off out there.

784
01:03:17,693 --> 01:03:21,185
<i>I slowly began to realize</i>
<i>I was not about to be destroyed.</i>

785
01:03:21,564 --> 01:03:23,031
The Chicago Bears.

786
01:03:23,633 --> 01:03:25,123
The terror of the midway.

787
01:03:26,102 --> 01:03:29,594
<i>From then on, things were different</i>
<i>between me and my mother.</i>

788
01:03:31,874 --> 01:03:34,934
More like the Chicago Chipmunks, maybe.

789
01:03:35,111 --> 01:03:36,237
But Bears, never.

790
01:03:38,214 --> 01:03:39,203
<i>Strange.</i>

791
01:03:39,482 --> 01:03:43,213
<i>Even something as monumental</i>
<i>as "The Scut Farkus Affair"...</i>

792
01:03:43,452 --> 01:03:44,976
<i>as it came to be known...</i>

793
01:03:45,154 --> 01:03:47,748
<i>was pushed out of my mind</i>
<i>as I struggled for a way out...</i>

794
01:03:47,824 --> 01:03:50,657
<i>of the impenetrable BB gun web...</i>

795
01:03:50,726 --> 01:03:52,785
<i>in which my mother had me trapped.</i>

796
01:03:53,129 --> 01:03:54,221
Santa!

797
01:03:54,931 --> 01:03:56,660
Yeah, I'll ask Santa.

798
01:03:57,366 --> 01:03:59,027
<i>Of course! Santa.</i>

799
01:03:59,335 --> 01:04:01,394
<i>The big man. The head honcho.</i>

800
01:04:01,637 --> 01:04:02,865
<i>The connection.</i>

801
01:04:03,139 --> 01:04:05,733
<i>My mother had slipped up this time.</i>

802
01:04:27,897 --> 01:04:29,524
Mickey!

803
01:04:46,582 --> 01:04:49,142
The store's going to close soon
and Santa will be gone.

804
01:04:49,218 --> 01:04:53,245
Ralphie, Santa's not going anyplace.
Just be still!

805
01:05:02,899 --> 01:05:05,333
Mom, this is just
the same old dumb parade as last year.

806
01:05:05,434 --> 01:05:08,631
- Ralphie, will you please calm down.
- Mom...

807
01:05:09,038 --> 01:05:10,665
- Hush!
- Shut up, Ralphie!

808
01:05:20,283 --> 01:05:21,079
There he is!

809
01:05:21,150 --> 01:05:23,311
Santa!

810
01:05:30,626 --> 01:05:33,117
Have you been a good boy? Have you?

811
01:05:33,262 --> 01:05:36,095
- Can we go now? Can we go?
- Yes, we can go now.

812
01:05:36,232 --> 01:05:38,427
Come on, Ralphie.

813
01:05:50,079 --> 01:05:52,172
Merry Christmas!

814
01:05:54,884 --> 01:05:57,250
Come on, Randy, hurry up.

815
01:06:10,366 --> 01:06:12,561
Ralphie, look over there.

816
01:06:12,635 --> 01:06:15,661
See, the line's not so long. Get in it.

817
01:06:15,738 --> 01:06:18,605
Take Randy's hand and hold on to him.
We'll see you later, okay?

818
01:06:18,674 --> 01:06:21,837
Stay together, you hear?
And don't get lost.

819
01:06:25,414 --> 01:06:26,506
Come on.

820
01:06:26,649 --> 01:06:28,116
Let's go.

821
01:06:31,020 --> 01:06:32,647
Young man.

822
01:06:32,822 --> 01:06:33,948
Hey, kid.

823
01:06:34,323 --> 01:06:37,884
- Just where do you think you're going?
- We're going up to see Santa.

824
01:06:38,728 --> 01:06:41,526
The line ends here. It begins there.

825
01:06:41,964 --> 01:06:43,659
Merry Christmas!

826
01:06:43,866 --> 01:06:46,960
Come on, come up, boys and girls.
Hurry up.

827
01:06:52,875 --> 01:06:54,308
Come on.

828
01:06:58,214 --> 01:07:03,015
<i>The line waiting to see Santa stretched</i>
<i>all the way back to Terre Haute!</i>

829
01:07:03,652 --> 01:07:05,552
<i>And I was at the end of it.</i>

830
01:07:07,890 --> 01:07:09,949
I like Santa.

831
01:07:14,330 --> 01:07:16,525
<i>Let's face it. Most of us were scoffers.</i>

832
01:07:16,599 --> 01:07:21,627
<i>Moments before zero hour,</i>
<i>it did not pay to take chances.</i>

833
01:07:22,571 --> 01:07:26,701
The chocolate snowman eats little boys.

834
01:07:28,444 --> 01:07:30,002
My pretty<i>...</i>

835
01:07:30,246 --> 01:07:32,373
What a tasty little boy.

836
01:07:33,649 --> 01:07:36,550
Don't bother me. I'm thinking.

837
01:07:40,956 --> 01:07:43,083
I like <i>The Wizard of Oz.</i>

838
01:07:46,362 --> 01:07:48,296
I like the Tin Man.

839
01:07:52,501 --> 01:07:56,597
If Higbee thinks I'm working one minute
past 9:00, he can kiss my foot.

840
01:07:58,240 --> 01:08:00,299
Come on up on Santa's lap.

841
01:08:00,409 --> 01:08:04,846
There's a wet one.
And what's your name, little boy?

842
01:08:05,047 --> 01:08:06,036
Billy.

843
01:08:06,115 --> 01:08:07,309
Come on, Randy.

844
01:08:08,884 --> 01:08:12,081
And what do you want for Christmas,
Billy? A toy truck?

845
01:08:12,188 --> 01:08:14,122
Get him off my lap.

846
01:08:14,256 --> 01:08:16,053
Quick, get me a towel.

847
01:08:23,799 --> 01:08:25,892
I hate the smell of tapioca.

848
01:08:27,436 --> 01:08:30,872
<i>Attention shoppers! It is now 9:00</i>
<i>and our store is closing.</i>

849
01:08:31,273 --> 01:08:34,208
<i>9:00! Great Scott!</i>
<i>The store is gonna close!</i>

850
01:08:35,244 --> 01:08:37,838
Santa can't wait all night.

851
01:08:38,414 --> 01:08:40,507
Come on up on Santa's lap.

852
01:08:50,292 --> 01:08:51,418
Get moving, kid.

853
01:08:52,761 --> 01:08:54,456
Quit dragging your feet.

854
01:09:07,576 --> 01:09:09,134
Get him out of here.

855
01:09:19,855 --> 01:09:21,618
Come on, kid.

856
01:09:27,696 --> 01:09:30,187
Come on up.

857
01:09:40,543 --> 01:09:44,035
And what's your name, little boy?

858
01:09:44,180 --> 01:09:47,616
Hey, kid, hurry up, the store's closing!

859
01:09:50,653 --> 01:09:55,317
Listen, little boy, we got
a lot of people waiting here, so get going!

860
01:09:57,526 --> 01:10:00,495
What do you want for Christmas,
little boy?

861
01:10:00,863 --> 01:10:02,956
<i>My mind had gone blank.</i>

862
01:10:03,098 --> 01:10:05,328
<i>Frantically I tried to remember</i>
<i>what it was I wanted.</i>

863
01:10:05,401 --> 01:10:06,959
<i>I was blowing it, blowing it.</i>

864
01:10:10,005 --> 01:10:13,065
How about a nice football?

865
01:10:13,209 --> 01:10:16,201
<i>Football. What's a football?</i>

866
01:10:16,912 --> 01:10:19,039
<i>Without conscious will,</i>
<i>my voice squeaked out:</i>

867
01:10:19,148 --> 01:10:20,376
Football.

868
01:10:20,916 --> 01:10:22,508
Okay, get him out of here.

869
01:10:23,052 --> 01:10:26,385
<i>A football! Oh, no. What was I doing?</i>

870
01:10:26,455 --> 01:10:28,821
<i>Wake up, stupid, wake up!</i>

871
01:10:36,632 --> 01:10:39,726
I want an official Red Ryder
carbine-action 200-shot...

872
01:10:39,835 --> 01:10:40,893
range model air rifle.

873
01:10:42,972 --> 01:10:44,667
You'll shoot your eye out, kid.

874
01:10:46,408 --> 01:10:48,205
Merry Christmas.

875
01:11:03,926 --> 01:11:05,723
I'll see you in Oz, folks.

876
01:11:14,303 --> 01:11:16,271
Well, did you see Santa Claus?

877
01:11:16,839 --> 01:11:19,273
Did you tell him
what you wanted for Christmas?

878
01:11:19,375 --> 01:11:23,106
Did he ask you if you'd been
a good boy all year?

879
01:11:23,512 --> 01:11:24,240
No.

880
01:11:25,080 --> 01:11:27,207
Don't worry, he knows.

881
01:11:27,916 --> 01:11:29,440
He always knows.

882
01:11:32,221 --> 01:11:34,849
Merry Christmas.

883
01:11:35,791 --> 01:11:38,123
Okay, down you go.

884
01:11:38,394 --> 01:11:39,554
Bye, Chris.

885
01:11:49,905 --> 01:11:52,203
That's fine.

886
01:11:53,008 --> 01:11:55,568
Now wait a minute. All right. Plug her in!

887
01:11:57,479 --> 01:11:59,106
Well, the green string is out.

888
01:11:59,214 --> 01:12:01,478
No, the green is on. It's the blue that's out.

889
01:12:01,750 --> 01:12:03,843
Oh, don't tell me what color it is.

890
01:12:03,952 --> 01:12:05,112
I'm not color blind.

891
01:12:05,888 --> 01:12:07,378
I'm not color blind, either.

892
01:12:11,060 --> 01:12:12,550
There, see, I told you it was green.

893
01:12:15,064 --> 01:12:17,191
Hold it! Don't anybody move!

894
01:12:18,667 --> 01:12:20,066
Hold it right there!

895
01:12:20,703 --> 01:12:22,466
