896
01:12:22,971 --> 01:12:26,668
<i>The old man could replace fuses</i>
<i>quicker than a jackrabbit on a date.</i>

897
01:12:26,742 --> 01:12:28,369
<i>He bought them by the gross.</i>

898
01:12:34,283 --> 01:12:36,012
Oh, Ralph.

899
01:12:36,318 --> 01:12:38,684
My, isn't that pretty?

900
01:12:38,854 --> 01:12:40,151
That son of a gun.

901
01:12:42,124 --> 01:12:43,318
Yeah. No.

902
01:12:43,459 --> 01:12:45,120
That star is crooked.

903
01:12:45,394 --> 01:12:47,328
That star is perfectly straight.

904
01:12:49,832 --> 01:12:51,925
- Oh, you've got to be careful.
- I am.

905
01:12:54,636 --> 01:12:57,764
It's just<i>...</i> Let me get it fixed.
That's all right.

906
01:13:03,846 --> 01:13:05,370
Perfect.

907
01:13:08,250 --> 01:13:10,081
Oh, goodness, look at the time.

908
01:13:10,152 --> 01:13:12,143
I hope Santa hasn't had to pass up
this house...

909
01:13:12,221 --> 01:13:15,247
just because some boys
weren't in bed when he came by.

910
01:13:15,391 --> 01:13:17,985
I thought I heard Santa's sleigh bells...

911
01:13:18,060 --> 01:13:20,585
a little while ago,
going up the other side of the street.

912
01:13:21,663 --> 01:13:22,994
All right, you two, upstairs.

913
01:13:24,133 --> 01:13:26,158
Go on the double, on the double.

914
01:13:37,679 --> 01:13:38,771
Okay, let's get them.

915
01:14:42,144 --> 01:14:44,203
Randy, come on! Get up, Randy!

916
01:14:54,923 --> 01:14:57,016
<i>Santa Claus had come!</i>

917
01:15:00,596 --> 01:15:02,791
Wow! A truck! That's mine!

918
01:15:03,365 --> 01:15:05,595
Wow, look over here! That's mine!

919
01:15:05,667 --> 01:15:07,157
What's in here?

920
01:15:07,503 --> 01:15:08,527
It's hard.

921
01:15:08,871 --> 01:15:11,931
Fire truck. Oh boy, that's mine!

922
01:15:21,016 --> 01:15:22,313
Does this raise?

923
01:15:37,499 --> 01:15:38,727
Merry Christmas.

924
01:15:40,202 --> 01:15:42,534
Merry Christmas, you two.

925
01:15:43,338 --> 01:15:46,034
Randy, no.
Wait for Christmas to start, honey.

926
01:15:46,475 --> 01:15:49,535
- I want to play Santa!
- Well, wait a minute, Randy.

927
01:15:49,611 --> 01:15:51,511
He played Santa last year, didn't he?

928
01:15:51,880 --> 01:15:54,007
Ralphie, you play Santa this time.

929
01:15:54,283 --> 01:15:56,217
- Come on, Ralphie.
- Who should I start with?

930
01:15:56,518 --> 01:15:58,816
Well, give Randy a present.

931
01:15:58,921 --> 01:16:03,085
And, I think I see Aunt Clara's gift to you
right over there.

932
01:16:03,191 --> 01:16:05,625
She always sends you
such wonderful presents.

933
01:16:05,994 --> 01:16:08,690
Give me mine, Ralphie! Come on.

934
01:16:25,581 --> 01:16:30,075
<i>Christmas had come. Officially.</i>
<i>We plunged into the cornucopia...</i>

935
01:16:30,152 --> 01:16:34,020
<i>quivering with desire</i>
<i>and the ecstasy of unbridled avarice.</i>

936
01:16:34,156 --> 01:16:35,589
Didn't I get a tie this year?

937
01:16:42,731 --> 01:16:46,030
- A zeppelin!
- A can of Simonize.

938
01:16:46,835 --> 01:16:49,998
Ralphie, what did Aunt Clara give you?
Show everybody.

939
01:16:55,177 --> 01:16:56,041
I don't want to.

940
01:16:56,645 --> 01:16:59,079
Ralphie, show everybody
what Aunt Clara gave you.

941
01:17:00,015 --> 01:17:02,848
<i>Aunt Clara had for years labored</i>
<i>under the delusion that...</i>

942
01:17:02,918 --> 01:17:07,446
<i>I was not only perpetually four years old,</i>
<i>but also a girl.</i>

943
01:17:07,956 --> 01:17:11,824
She just always gives you
the nicest things, Ralphie.

944
01:17:16,331 --> 01:17:19,129
Oh, isn't that sweet?

945
01:17:19,568 --> 01:17:22,366
- Ralph, go upstairs and try it on you...
- I don't want to!

946
01:17:22,471 --> 01:17:24,871
Go upstairs right now
and try on that present!

947
01:17:24,973 --> 01:17:28,340
She went to all that trouble to make it!
Now go on.

948
01:17:36,018 --> 01:17:40,182
While Ralphie is changing,
I'm going to play Santa Claus.

949
01:17:40,255 --> 01:17:41,882
Now, let me see what can I find.

950
01:17:42,090 --> 01:17:45,651
I see something! Randy.

951
01:17:45,894 --> 01:17:47,657
This is for you, honey.

952
01:17:48,530 --> 01:17:50,464
And this is for Daddy.

953
01:17:53,402 --> 01:17:54,096
Here.

954
01:17:54,169 --> 01:17:56,034
From me to you.

955
01:17:58,306 --> 01:18:00,137
Thanks a lot.

956
01:18:00,542 --> 01:18:02,772
I wonder what it could be?

957
01:18:03,779 --> 01:18:06,771
Only one way to find out, isn't there?

958
01:18:07,049 --> 01:18:09,244
Well, it's a blue ball!

959
01:18:10,919 --> 01:18:12,682
It's a bowling ball.

960
01:18:13,689 --> 01:18:14,951
Thank you, darling.

961
01:18:15,057 --> 01:18:18,185
- Do you like it?
- Yes, very much. Very much.

962
01:18:18,894 --> 01:18:19,792
Ralphie.

963
01:18:19,995 --> 01:18:22,020
We're waiting.

964
01:18:22,197 --> 01:18:23,755
Oh, come on, Mom.

965
01:18:24,199 --> 01:18:25,860
Right now!

966
01:18:35,944 --> 01:18:39,573
<i>lmmediately my feet began to sweat</i>
<i>as those two fluffy little bunnies...</i>

967
01:18:39,648 --> 01:18:43,015
<i>with the blue button eyes</i>
<i>stared sappily up at me.</i>

968
01:18:43,752 --> 01:18:46,448
Come down here so I can see you better.

969
01:18:47,289 --> 01:18:49,086
<i>I just hoped Flick would never spot them...</i>

970
01:18:49,224 --> 01:18:52,523
<i>as the word of this humiliation</i>
<i>could easily make life...</i>

971
01:18:52,594 --> 01:18:55,427
<i>at Warren G. Harding School</i>
<i>a veritable hell.</i>

972
01:18:57,866 --> 01:18:58,855
Isn't that cute?

973
01:18:59,534 --> 01:19:03,163
That is the most precious thing
I've ever seen in my life.

974
01:19:03,972 --> 01:19:04,870
Shut up, Randy.

975
01:19:05,874 --> 01:19:07,967
He looks like a deranged Easter bunny.

976
01:19:10,178 --> 01:19:11,873
- He does not!
- He does, too.

977
01:19:11,947 --> 01:19:13,642
He looks like a pink nightmare.

978
01:19:14,316 --> 01:19:16,307
Are you happy wearing that?

979
01:19:16,651 --> 01:19:17,640
Do you want to take it off?

980
01:19:17,853 --> 01:19:19,081
You tell the kid to take it off.

981
01:19:19,154 --> 01:19:22,123
You'll only wear it when Aunt Clara visits.
Go on and take it off.

982
01:19:22,190 --> 01:19:23,851
Take it off!

983
01:19:27,462 --> 01:19:29,362
My God, will you look at that mess?

984
01:19:29,765 --> 01:19:32,199
- Who's going to clean the papers up?
- Not me.

985
01:19:33,602 --> 01:19:35,934
- Randy did it last year.
- Well, he can do it again.

986
01:19:38,507 --> 01:19:41,408
You know, this wine is not bad.
It's not good either, but<i>...</i>

987
01:19:41,476 --> 01:19:44,036
- You want a sip?
- No, you don't.

988
01:19:45,514 --> 01:19:46,606
Did you have a nice Christmas?

989
01:19:47,349 --> 01:19:48,316
Yeah, pretty nice.

990
01:19:48,416 --> 01:19:49,883
Did you get everything you wanted?

991
01:19:50,852 --> 01:19:53,514
- Well, almost.
- Almost?

992
01:19:53,622 --> 01:19:55,249
Well, that's life.

993
01:19:55,924 --> 01:19:57,619
Well, there's always next Christmas.

994
01:20:00,862 --> 01:20:02,227
That's funny.

995
01:20:03,131 --> 01:20:04,928
What's that over there behind the desk?

996
01:20:05,967 --> 01:20:06,899
Where?

997
01:20:06,968 --> 01:20:08,799
Behind the desk,
against the wall over there.

998
01:20:11,640 --> 01:20:12,971
Why don't you go check it out?

999
01:20:29,658 --> 01:20:30,955
What did we put over there, honey?

1000
01:20:32,427 --> 01:20:34,520
Santa Claus probably put it.

1001
01:21:11,399 --> 01:21:15,233
<i>Oh, it was beautiful.</i>
<i>I could hardly wait to try it out.</i>

1002
01:21:16,004 --> 01:21:17,665
Do you know how to load it?

1003
01:21:21,109 --> 01:21:22,371
That's right.

1004
01:21:30,051 --> 01:21:30,949
Be careful.

1005
01:21:31,419 --> 01:21:32,852
Don't. They run all over.

1006
01:21:39,694 --> 01:21:40,956
Close her up. Close it up.

1007
01:21:42,030 --> 01:21:44,726
Can I try it out, Ma? Can I?

1008
01:21:44,833 --> 01:21:46,300
- Sure.
- Okay.

1009
01:21:46,768 --> 01:21:47,894
But outside.

1010
01:21:48,003 --> 01:21:49,868
I still say those things are dangerous.

1011
01:21:51,373 --> 01:21:53,967
Put on your galoshes and your coat.
It's cold out.

1012
01:21:57,412 --> 01:22:00,347
I had one when I was eight years old.

1013
01:22:00,949 --> 01:22:03,474
What if he hurts himself?
Ralphie, your coat!

1014
01:22:04,786 --> 01:22:08,688
- Don't shoot any animals or birds!
- Except the Bumpuses' dogs!

1015
01:22:10,292 --> 01:22:12,283
Be careful, Ralphie!

1016
01:22:12,961 --> 01:22:16,055
<i>Now it is well known throughout</i>
<i>the Midwest that the old man...</i>

1017
01:22:16,131 --> 01:22:17,996
<i>is a turkey junkie.</i>

1018
01:22:18,867 --> 01:22:23,167
<i>A bona fide garley turkicanus freak.</i>
<i>A few days before Christmas...</i>

1019
01:22:23,305 --> 01:22:27,401
<i>his eyes would begin to gleam</i>
<i>with a wild and ravenous light.</i>

1020
01:22:31,379 --> 01:22:35,679
Okay, Black Bart, now you get yours.

1021
01:22:49,664 --> 01:22:51,598
<i>Oh, my God! I shot my eye out!</i>

1022
01:22:51,766 --> 01:22:53,324
<i>You'll shoot your eye out, kid.</i>

1023
01:22:53,802 --> 01:22:58,068
<i>You'll shoot your eye out,</i>
<i>you'll shoot your eye out!</i>

1024
01:22:59,007 --> 01:23:02,204
Ralphie, you be careful out there.
Don't shoot your eye out!

1025
01:23:02,277 --> 01:23:04,336
<i>She hadn't seen! She didn't know!</i>

1026
01:23:04,980 --> 01:23:07,574
<i>My eye's all right.</i>
<i>The BB must've hit my glasses.</i>

1027
01:23:08,984 --> 01:23:10,679
<i>My glasses! Oh, no!</i>

1028
01:23:10,752 --> 01:23:12,413
<i>Where are my glasses?</i>

1029
01:23:14,055 --> 01:23:16,819
<i>Few things brought such swift</i>
<i>and terrible retribution...</i>

1030
01:23:16,925 --> 01:23:19,894
<i>on a kid as a pair of busted glasses!</i>

1031
01:23:24,232 --> 01:23:25,494
Stop!

1032
01:23:37,712 --> 01:23:39,179
Oh, no!

1033
01:23:41,649 --> 01:23:43,913
<i>Oh, no! Pulverized.</i>

1034
01:23:55,797 --> 01:23:59,961
<i>For a moment I thought, I'll fake it.</i>
<i>They'll never know the lens is gone!</i>

1035
01:24:02,637 --> 01:24:05,470
<i>Randomly, my mind evolved</i>
<i>a spectacular plot.</i>

1036
01:24:05,673 --> 01:24:07,834
<i>Let's see, an icicle!</i>

1037
01:24:08,176 --> 01:24:10,542
<i>Falls off the garage and hits me in the eye!</i>

1038
01:24:10,879 --> 01:24:15,077
<i>It would work. It had to work.</i>
<i>Quickly, I whipped up some tears.</i>

1039
01:24:21,356 --> 01:24:24,120
What's the matter, honey?
What happened?

1040
01:24:24,192 --> 01:24:25,420
What happened? Let me see that.

1041
01:24:25,493 --> 01:24:29,259
There was this icicle
and it fell off the garage and it hit me.

1042
01:24:33,635 --> 01:24:36,866
- What is it?
- No, it's okay. Just read your funnies.

1043
01:24:41,042 --> 01:24:42,532
Wake up, Randy.

1044
01:24:47,315 --> 01:24:48,646
Oh, God.

1045
01:24:48,817 --> 01:24:51,877
It hit my cheek and it broke my glasses.

1046
01:24:52,387 --> 01:24:56,084
And I tried to get out of the way, but I<i>...</i>

1047
01:24:58,026 --> 01:25:01,928
There, see, it's just a little bump.

1048
01:25:02,297 --> 01:25:03,958
You're lucky it didn't cut your eye.

1049
01:25:04,032 --> 01:25:06,159
Those icicles have been known
to kill people.

1050
01:25:12,407 --> 01:25:15,808
- What's going on up there?
- Nothing. We'll be right down.

1051
01:25:16,111 --> 01:25:18,773
You stay away from that turkey!
It's got an hour to cook.

1052
01:25:18,880 --> 01:25:20,040
You'll get worms!

1053
01:25:25,220 --> 01:25:26,710
But what about my glasses?

1054
01:25:27,288 --> 01:25:29,620
You can wear the old ones
with the crack in them...

1055
01:25:29,691 --> 01:25:31,522
until we get you some new ones.

1056
01:25:34,362 --> 01:25:36,262
<i>I had pulled it off!</i>

1057
01:25:37,665 --> 01:25:39,530
But I left my gun outside.

1058
01:25:40,835 --> 01:25:43,702
When you get dressed
you can go out and get your gun.

1059
01:25:43,905 --> 01:25:45,270
Hold that on there.

1060
01:25:45,773 --> 01:25:47,365
<i>Life is like that.</i>

1061
01:25:47,842 --> 01:25:52,779
<i>Sometimes at the height of our reveries,</i>
<i>when our joy is at its zenith...</i>

1062
01:25:52,881 --> 01:25:55,782
<i>when all is most right with the world...</i>

1063
01:25:55,917 --> 01:25:59,250
<i>the most unthinkable disasters</i>
<i>descend upon us.</i>

1064
01:26:14,702 --> 01:26:16,260
Oh, turkey!

1065
01:26:31,119 --> 01:26:34,316
Sons a bitches! Bumpuses!

1066
01:26:49,537 --> 01:26:53,132
<i>The heavenly aroma still hung heavy</i>
<i>in the house. But it was gone.</i>

1067
01:26:53,274 --> 01:26:56,300
<i>All gone. No turkey.</i>
<i>No turkey sandwiches.</i>

1068
01:26:56,377 --> 01:27:00,404
<i>No turkey salad. No turkey gravy,</i>
<i>turkey hash, turkey à la king...</i>

1069
01:27:00,515 --> 01:27:01,812
<i>or gallons of turkey soup.</i>

1070
01:27:01,883 --> 01:27:02,611
<i>Gone.</i>

1071
01:27:02,684 --> 01:27:03,946
<i>All gone.</i>

1072
01:27:08,590 --> 01:27:09,579
All right.

1073
01:27:10,058 --> 01:27:10,956
Everybody upstairs.

1074
01:27:11,192 --> 01:27:12,489
Get dressed.

1075
01:27:14,662 --> 01:27:16,152
We are going out to eat.

1076
01:27:40,455 --> 01:27:44,915
No! Not, '<i>'</i>ra ra ra ra ra.'<i>'</i> '<i>'</i>La la la la la.'<i>'</i>

1077
01:27:45,326 --> 01:27:46,122
Sing like this:

1078
01:27:54,569 --> 01:27:56,059
Try again.

1079
01:28:06,080 --> 01:28:07,274
Stop!

1080
01:28:08,049 --> 01:28:09,812
Sing something else.

1081
01:28:23,398 --> 01:28:24,456
No!

1082
01:28:24,532 --> 01:28:25,624
Stop!

1083
01:28:26,501 --> 01:28:28,765
Kitchen. Bring food. For customers.

1084
01:28:37,912 --> 01:28:39,243
Oh, I'm sorry.

1085
01:28:42,083 --> 01:28:43,744
It's a beautiful duck.

1086
01:28:44,152 --> 01:28:45,813
It really is.

1087
01:28:46,621 --> 01:28:48,248
But you see<i>...</i>

1088
01:28:50,758 --> 01:28:51,554
What?

1089
01:28:51,626 --> 01:28:53,594
It's smiling at me.

1090
01:28:59,167 --> 01:29:00,259
Okay?

1091
01:29:01,669 --> 01:29:03,102
Beautiful!

1092
01:29:06,641 --> 01:29:08,666
<i>That Christmas would live</i>
<i>in our memories...</i>

1093
01:29:08,776 --> 01:29:12,212
<i>as the Christmas when</i>
<i>we were introduced to Chinese turkey.</i>

1094
01:29:13,648 --> 01:29:15,639
<i>All was right with the world.</i>

1095
01:29:36,604 --> 01:29:38,902
Oh, honey, come over here. Look at this.

1096
01:29:39,741 --> 01:29:41,709
Is that beautiful!

1097
01:30:27,655 --> 01:30:31,921
<i>Next to me in the blackness</i>
<i>lay my oiled blue-steel beauty.</i>

1098
01:30:32,693 --> 01:30:35,025
<i>The greatest Christmas gift</i>
<i>I had ever received...</i>

1099
01:30:35,129 --> 01:30:36,562
<i>or would ever receive.</i>

1100
01:30:37,732 --> 01:30:41,395
<i>Gradually, I drifted off to sleep,</i>
<i>pranging ducks on the wing...</i>

1101
01:30:41,469 --> 01:30:43,994
<i>and getting off spectacular hip shots.</i>

1102
01:33:17,391 --> 01:33:18,688
English

